Prevent prototype pollution:

```javascript
// 1. Create null-prototype objects
const obj = Object.create(null);

// 2. Freeze the prototype
Object.freeze(Object.prototype);

// 3. Validate keys before setting
if (key !== '__proto__' && key !== 'constructor' && key !== 'prototype') {
obj[key] = value;
}
```

Rewrite the regex to avoid catastrophic backtracking:
```javascript
// Instead of:
const regex = /(a+)+$/;  // Vulnerable!

// Use:
const regex = /a+$/;  // Non-nested quantifier

// Or use possessive quantifiers (if supported):
// Or add input length limits before regex matching:
if (input.length > 1000) throw new Error('Input too long');
```

